caption.text:
I’ll tell you a story not many people know 👇

My account has 1.3 million followers right now.

In February 2021, exactly 3 years ago, I created this account. 

I had 0 followers and 0 posts but a huge desire to build a personal brand and start selling my online products. 

I started posting reels daily. But for the first 3 months, I saw almost no growth. 

It was tough. I was spending countless hours on content creation but getting no views and no new followers. 

But I remember that moment vividly. I was about to post yet another reel, and I wasn’t 100% satisfied with its quality and how it was shot. 

Remaking that video meant spending 1-2 more hours of my time. I needed to go back to the mall, shoot again, then go outside where it was 30 degrees Fahrenheit, and shoot again, then edit everything. 

I could have just said, “Screw it. I know it’s not going to get views anyway.” But instead, I put in that extra push to make my video a little bit better, and then I posted it. 

Guess what happened next? 

That video got over 100k views overnight and, in 7 days, 1 million views. 

Three years later, I have 3 IG accounts in 3 different languages with an audience of almost 2 million followers, and I run a multi-seven-figure coaching/service social media company. 

All because of Instagram. 

But it all started from that moment. I knew that if I kept pushing, the results would come. 

So don’t give up, don’t settle—keep pushing. You might be one step away from “overnight success”

Share this reel with someone who needs to hear that

The more viral videos we have, the more recreated viral videos we have, and the more good content we post, the more we grow.

That’s how we helped him to triple his followers in a matter of a few weeks
